<DOC><DOCNO> AP881212-0059 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-12-88 0658EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Lebanon-Violence     12-12 0183</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Lebanon-Violence,0191</SECOND><HEAD>Belgian Educator Murdered</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Gunmen using silencer-equipped pistolsshot and killed a Belgian teacher in Moslem west Beirut today,police said.   They identified the victim as Arthur Van Niewerburgh, an Englishteacher at west Beirut's Rashideen School of Languages.   Niewerburgh, 65, was walking from school to his home in theManara district when he was shot by gunmen in a speeding car at 11a.m., police said.   ``Four bullets pierced his head. Death was instantaneous,'' saida police spokesman who cannot be named under standing regulations.   He said witnesses told police they saw three gunmen in the orangeVolvo used in the assassination. The car did not have licenceplates, police said.   Niewerburgh's body was still lying in a pool of blood on a Manarasidewalk two hours after the shooting as police interrogatedwitnesses.   His head was covered with a blood-soaked towel.   Niewerburgh is survived by a Japanese wife and a 15-year-old son,Christian.   His wife, whose name was not immediately available, was abroad onvacation. She owns the Tokyo Restaurant in west Beirut, police said.</TEXT></DOC>